There was a twilight zone a lot like this, can't think of the name…

As for her "powers", we have several options:

continue to utilize the "witch" control mechanism, funneling her power through a "spell book". This will allow us to somewhat channel her growth.
Put her into stats, or a prolonged coma state. From there, possible neutralization or continued containment as-is could be discussed.
Attempt to cause SCP-239 to "forget" or lose her power by causing her to "wish" them away.


Any of these options has numerous applications, both positive and negative. However, I express concern over the proposal of using SCP-239 to "wish" other SCP items into a controllable or non-existent state. We do not know if the changes are permanent, nor what effect it may have on each item. Also, if she sees her ability to alter such items, SCP-239 may begin to wonder what else she can do, and question her captivity.







